        "id": 2958097,
        "name": "Greg Kramer",
        "username": "Greg_Kramer",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/greg_kramer/{size}/955_2.png",
        "created_at": "2020-08-16T16:22:44.000Z",
        "cooked": "<ul>\n<li>\n<a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com/note.asp?iWine=26013&amp;iNote=8571007\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"><strong>1975 Ch\u00e2teau Meyney</strong></a> <em>- France, Bordeaux, M\u00e9doc, St. Est\u00e8phe (8/8/2020)</em><br>\nForever to be known as the miracle wine. Several months ago, I noticed this was leaking. Stood it up and finally got around to opening. Removed the foil to discover the cork was fully dislodged. What I thought was an excellent fill level (despite the awful storage conditions this endured) was really the just the cork. The color was decent and while hardly charming (don\u2019t know if too many from this vintage are) it was still wine and rather enjoyable if you like really mature wine flavors.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><em>Posted from <a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com/\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">CellarTracker</a></em></p>",
