        "id": 2958854,
        "name": "Anthony Curtas ",
        "username": "Anthony_C",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/anthony_c/{size}/3429_2.png",
        "created_at": "2020-08-17T18:07:31.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I haven\u2019t had a lot of 75\u2019s but the Picon Lalande Comtesse was great, stood out against a few others I\u2019ve tried.  Definitely the earliest Bordeaux vintage I sampled more than one of.  I have a few more bottles left.  It\u2019s definitely through its drinking window, but I\u2019ve been patient drinking them.</p>\n<p>I\u2019ll keep an eye out for the Latour.  Seems to be under $500 if you can find them.  While out of my price range, there\u2019s always special occasions <img src=\"/images/emoji/unicode/slight_smile.png?v=12\" title=\":slight_smile:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":slight_smile:\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\"></p>",
